Class PrimalDecompDeviation

  • java.lang.Object
    • tum.dss.thesis.lsframework.PrimalDecompDeviation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PrimalDecompositionInterface

    public class PrimalDecompDeviation
extends Object
implements PrimalDecompositionInterface
    Modified primal LP of the convex decomposition which minimizes the absolute deviation as Gurobi Model.
    Author:
    Florian Stallmann

        public boolean testFeasibility()
        Description copied from interface: PrimalDecompositionInterface
        Test if LP model is already feasible.

        The createLP needs to be called before to update the current model. Otherwise (without model) the method will always return false.

      • getExpectedSocialWelfare

        public double getExpectedSocialWelfare()
        Description copied from interface: PrimalDecompositionInterface
        Returns the calculated expected social welfare.

        The solveLP method must be called before!

        The return value should be equal to the optimal social welfare divided by the integrality gap of the separation oracle. A validation of this is performed in the AbstractMechanism.step3SolvePrimal() method.

        Specified by:
        getExpectedSocialWelfare in interface PrimalDecompositionInterface
        Returns:
        social welfare.

      • getObjective

        public double getObjective()
        Description copied from interface: PrimalDecompositionInterface
        Retrieves objective value of the LP.

        The solveLP method must be called before! This value should always be 1, otherwise something went wrong.

        Specified by:
        getObjective in interface PrimalDecompositionInterface
